urlText: Opal can be used between Wollongong and Moss Vale, Exeter and Bundanoon stations.
content:
If travelling by Coach between Wollongong station and Moss Vale, Exeter or Bundanoon stations you can use your Opal card or contactless card or device to tap on or off at your origin/destination station provided the origin/destination is an Opal enabled station.

If travelling onto Goulburn, or other Opal enabled station along the Southern Highlands Line, you should not tap off when transferring from Coach to an Intercity train but instead tap off at your destination station.

Booking is not required for Opal customers on this route.

urlText: North Parramatta, temporary bus stop closures
content:

  • Bus stops Our Lady of Mercy College, O’Connell St (2150152) and Victoria Rd after Villiers St (2150108) will be closed. The alternative stop will be All Saints’ Anglican Church, Victoria Rd (215088).
Services away from Parramatta:
  • Bus stop Grose St after Sorrell St (2150126) will be closed. The alternative stop will be Brickfield St at Fennell St (215082) for the 546 towards Epping and the 552 towards Oatlands.
  • Bus stops Victoria Rd before Marist Place (2150110) and Parramatta Leagues Club, O’Connell St will be closed. The alternative stop will be Victoria Rd opposite All Saints’ Anglican Church (215089) for the 546 towards Epping and the 552 towards Oatlands.
